Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Otunba Adeniyi Adebayo, has tested negative to COVID-19. He confirmed that the result of his COVID-19 test has come out negative, adding that the test was carried out by the Nigeria Centre for Disease and Control (NCDC). In a statement signed by SA Media, to the Honourable Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Toba Jegede, on Friday in Abuja, he said, “The decision to carry out the test was premised on the minister’s recent contact with someone who had met with a top functionary who reportedly tested positive to the virus, during an official assignment. “The minister also called on all Nigerians to comply with the National Center for Disease Control (NCDC) extant guidelines and directives given out by the Government from time to time,” he said.